          version="5.0-subset Scilab"
          xml:id="XcosMenuAlign">
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>Align</refname>
    <refpurpose>Menu: Aligns block ports</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      To obtain nice diagrams, you can align ports of different
      blocks, vertically and horizontally. 
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Usage</title>
    <para>
      Select first the Align
      menu item, then click on the first port and finally on the
      second port.  The block corresponding to the second port is
      moved.  
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Restriction</title>
    <para> A connected block cannot be aligned. So it is better to align blocks before connecting them.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>See Also</title>
